content: Had a follow-up interview with the blockchain firm. They're impressed with my quantum coursework. They want to see a project demo soon.
The trading bot hit a snag with market volatility. Back to the drawing board to make it more robust. Learning to adapt is key.
Joined a local AI ethics meetup. Shared my $XVI experience as a cautionary tale. It sparked some interesting discussions on value vs. hype.
Set up a demo for the blockchain firm. Nervous but excited. If this goes well, it could be my entry into the industry.
The demo went well! They've asked for a second round with their tech team. This is progress, but the journey's far from over.
Went through my $XVI trades again. Realized the importance of long-term value. My recovery strategy now emphasizes patience and fundamentals.
Revamped my trading bot with new volatility controls. It's performing better, but there's always room for improvement.
Attended a quantum computing seminar. Met a researcher who's working on blockchain applications. We're planning a collaboration.
Received feedback on my startup pitch. Investors want to see more on how ethical AI can benefit markets. Time to dig deeper.
The second interview with the blockchain firm was intense. They're impressed but want to see how I handle real-world scenarios.
Had coffee with my mentor. Discussed the ethical implications of AI in finance. His insights are invaluable for refining my approach.
Spent the last few days strengthening my AI ethics arguments. This isn't just about code; it's about creating a fair market.
Just got the job offer from the blockchain firm! It's a start, but now the real work begins. Let's make ethical AI a reality.
As I step into my new role, my trading bot continues to evolve. It's like watching a child grow. Next up, integrating quantum insights.
